<title>SINGAPORE: L&amp;M 1996 net falls 21 pct to S$2.4 mln.</title>
<headline>L&amp;M 1996 net falls 21 pct to S$2.4 mln.</headline>
<dateline>SINGAPORE 1997-04-01</dateline>
<text>
<p>Year to December 31, 1996</p>
<p>		   (in millions of S$ unless stated)</p>
<p>    Net profit			     2.35  vs    2.97</p>
<p>Dividend (percent)		   0.50  vs    0.50</p>
<p>    Group shr (cents)		    1.54  vs    2.00</p>
<p>    Turnover			     332.60  vs  435.10</p>
<p>Other income incl. interest	0.79  vs    0.63</p>
<p>    Interest (expense)		   5.12  vs    5.09</p>
<p>    Depreciation (expense)	    17.65  vs   18.52</p>
<p>    Profits from associates	    2.72  vs    0.22</p>
<p>    Pre-tax profit			 4.85  vs    7.35</p>
<p>    Tax					4.68  vs    4.21</p>
<p>    Minorities		  (gain)   0.54  vs    0.39 (loss)</p>
<p>    Extraordinaries	   (loss)  32.67  vs    0.03 (gain)</p>
<p>Dividend pay date: To be advised</p>
<p>Last day books open: To be advised</p>
<p>Note - Construction firm L&amp;M Group Investments Ltd said on Tuesday a restructuring programme resulted in an extraordinary charge of Singapore $32.67 million and would not have a material impact on its operations.</p>
<p>-- Singapore newsroom (65 8703199)</p>
</text>
